    "version": "1.8",
    "release_notes": "Touch-Matrix Desynchronization Resolution (Bug Fixes): Addressed micro-stutters during rapid multi-touch interactions. The client-side architecture now utilizes rigorous input-event debouncing to filter out accidental duplicate touches, ensuring localized state execution remains flawless during high-speed interface navigation.\nAdvanced Vertex-Shader Execution (New Features): Deployed a highly optimized graphical processing algorithm. The localized engine now dynamically scales its vertex-shader execution, recalculating the geometry of complex UI assets on the fly to drastically reduce GPU bottlenecking during continuous visual transitions.",
